{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775844412114,"sessionID":"ses_2876d9678ffeULAajBxoo8YO8M","part":{"id":"prt_d789344ca001aFOb3tjhKvjbRB","messageID":"msg_d78932769001h8phx1AsncgBsn","sessionID":"ses_2876d9678ffeULAajBxoo8YO8M","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-c7ba9cdcdb584573a7fb6b08a9482cbd","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/workloadmanager/k8s_client_test.go"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/workloadmanager/k8s_client_test.go</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: package workloadmanager\n2: \n3: import (\n4: \t\"context\"\n5: \t\"testing\"\n6: \t\"time\"\n7: \n8: \t\"github.com/stretchr/testify/assert\"\n9: \t\"github.com/stretchr/testify/require\"\n10: \tcorev1 \"k8s.io/api/core/v1\"\n11: \tmetav1 \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1\"\n12: \t\"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime\"\n13: \tdynamicfake \"k8s.io/client-go/dynamic/fake\"\n14: \t\"k8s.io/client-go/informers\"\n15: \t\"k8s.io/client-go/kubernetes\"\n16: \t\"k8s.io/client-go/kubernetes/fake\"\n17: \t\"k8s.io/client-go/rest\"\n18: )\n19: \n20: func TestNewK8sClient(t *testing.T) {\n21: \tconfig := &rest.Config{\n22: \t\tHost: \"http://localhost:8080\",\n23: \t}\n24: \n25: \tclient, err := NewK8sClient(config)\n26: \trequire.NoError(t, err)\n27: \tassert.NotNil(t, client)\n28: \tassert.NotNil(t, client.dynamicClient)\n29: \tassert.NotNil(t, client.coreClient)\n30: \tassert.NotNil(t, client.informerFactory)\n31: \tassert.NotNil(t, client.podLister)\n32: }\n33: \n34: func TestK8sClient_StartInformers(t *testing.T) {\n35: \tfakeClient := fake.NewSimpleClientset()\n36: \n37: \tclient := &K8sClient{\n38: \t\tcoreClient:      fakeClient,\n39: \t\tinformerFactory: NewTestInformerFactory(fakeClient),\n40: \t}\n41: \n42: \tctx, cancel := context.WithTimeout(context.Background(), 5*time.Second)\n43: \tdefer cancel()\n44: \n45: \tclient.StartInformers(ctx)\n46: \n47: \tsynced := client.WaitForCacheSync(ctx)\n48: \tassert.True(t, synced)\n49: }\n50: \n51: func TestK8sClient_PodLister(t *testing.T) {\n52: \tpod := &corev1.Pod{\n53: \t\tObjectMeta: metav1.ObjectMeta{\n54: \t\t\tName:      \"test-pod\",\n55: \t\t\tNamespace: \"default\",\n56: \t\t},\n57: \t\tStatus: corev1.PodStatus{\n58: \t\t\tPhase: corev1.PodRunning,\n59: \t\t\tPodIP: \"10.244.0.5\",\n60: \t\t},\n61: \t}\n62: \n63: \tfakeClient := fake.NewSimpleClientset(pod)\n64: \tinformerFactory := NewTestInformerFactory(fakeClient)\n65: \n66: \tclient := &K8sClient{\n67: \t\tcoreClient:      fakeClient,\n68: \t\tinformerFactory: informerFactory,\n69: \t\tpodLister:       informerFactory.Core().V1().Pods().Lister(),\n70: \t}\n71: \n72: \tctx, cancel := context.WithTimeout(context.Background(), 5*time.Second)\n73: \tdefer cancel()\n74: \n75: \tclient.StartInformers(ctx)\n76: \tclient.WaitForCacheSync(ctx)\n77: \n78: \tretrievedPod, err := client.PodLister().Pods(\"default\").Get(\"test-pod\")\n79: \trequire.NoError(t, err)\n80: \tassert.Equal(t, \"test-pod\", retrievedPod.Name)\n81: \tassert.Equal(t, corev1.PodRunning, retrievedPod.Status.Phase)\n82: }\n83: \n84: func TestClientCache_GetOrCreateClient(t *testing.T) {\n85: \tcache := NewClientCache()\n86: \n87: \tconfig := &rest.Config{\n88: \t\tHost: \"http://localhost:8080\",\n89: \t}\n90: \n91: \tclient1, err := cache.GetOrCreateClient(\"token1\", \"ns1\", config)\n92: \trequire.NoError(t, err)\n93: \tassert.NotNil(t, client1)\n94: \n95: \tclient2, err := cache.GetOrCreateClient(\"token1\", \"ns1\", config)\n96: \trequire.NoError(t, err)\n97: \tassert.Equal(t, client1, client2, \"Should return same client for same token+namespace\")\n98: \n99: \tclient3, err := cache.GetOrCreateClient(\"token2\", \"ns2\", config)\n100: \trequire.NoError(t, err)\n101: \tassert.NotNil(t, client3)\n102: \tassert.NotEqual(t, client1, client3, \"Should return different client for different token+namespace\")\n103: }\n104: \n105: func NewTestInformerFactory(client kubernetes.Interface) informers.SharedInformerFactory {\n106: \treturn informers.NewSharedInformerFactoryWithOptions(\n107: \t\tclient,\n108: \t\ttime.Minute,\n109: \t)\n110: }\n111: \n112: func TestK8sClient_Methods(t *testing.T) {\n113: \tfakeClient := fake.NewSimpleClientset()\n114: \tinformerFactory := NewTestInformerFactory(fakeClient)\n115: \tdynamicClient := dynamicfake.NewSimpleDynamicClient(runtime.NewScheme())\n116: \n117: \tclient := &K8sClient{\n118: \t\tdynamicClient:   dynamicClient,\n119: \t\tcoreClient:      fakeClient,\n120: \t\tinformerFactory: informerFactory,\n121: \t\tpodLister:       informerFactory.Core().V1().Pods().Lister(),\n122: \t}\n123: \n124: \tassert.NotNil(t, client.DynamicClient())\n125: \tassert.NotNil(t, client.CoreClient())\n126: \tassert.NotNil(t, client.PodLister())\n127: \tassert.NotNil(t, client.InformerFactory())\n128: }\n\n(End of file - total 128 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"package workloadmanager\n\nimport (\n\t\"context\"\n\t\"testing\"\n\t\"time\"\n\n\t\"github.com/stretchr/testify/assert\"\n\t\"github.com/stretchr/testify/require\"\n\tcorev1 \"k8s.io/api/core/v1\"\n\tmetav1 \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1\"\n\t\"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime\"\n\tdynamicfake \"k8s.io/client-go/dynamic/fake\"\n\t\"k8s.io/client-go/informers\"\n\t\"k8s.io/client-go/kubernetes\"\n\t\"k8s.io/client-go/kubernetes/fake\"\n\t\"k8s.io/client-go/rest\"\n)\n\nfunc TestNewK8sClient(t *testing.T) {","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/workloadmanager/k8s_client_test.go","time":{"start":1775844412086,"end":1775844412113}}}}
